NALU initialization

Defining NALU

\[ \begin{aligned} a_{h_\ell} &= \sum_{h_{\ell-1}=1}^{H_{\ell-1}} W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} z_{h_{\ell-1}} \\ m_{h_\ell} &= \exp\left(\sum_{h_{\ell-1}=1}^{H_{\ell-1}} W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} \log(|z_{h_{\ell-1}}| + \epsilon) \right) \\ g_{h_\ell} &= \sigma(\hat{g}_{h_\ell}),\ \hat{g}_{h_\ell} = \sum_{h_{\ell-1}=1}^{H_{\ell-1}} G_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} z_{h_{\ell-1}} \\ z_{h_\ell} &= g_{h_\ell} a_{h_\ell} + (1 - g_{h_\ell}) m_{h_\ell} \\ \mathcal{L} &= \sum_{h_{L}=1}^{H_L} (z_{h_L} - t_{h_L})^2 \end{aligned} \]

We will not explicitly define \(W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}\) here, as \(Var[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}]\) can be generalized to any construction, and we assume \(E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}]\).

Forward

Deriving the expectation

Output expectation

\[ \begin{aligned} E[y_{h_\ell}] &= E[g_{h_\ell} a_{h_\ell} + (1 - g_{h_\ell}) m_{h_\ell}] \\ &= E[g_{h_\ell}] E[a_{h_\ell}] + E[1 - g_{h_\ell}] E[m_{h_\ell}] \\ &= E[g_{h_\ell}] E[a_{h_\ell}] + (1 - E[g_{h_\ell}]) E[m_{h_\ell}] \end{aligned} \] ### Gate expectation

\[ \begin{aligned} E[g_{h_\ell}] &= E[\sigma(\hat{g}_{h_\ell})] \\ &\approx \sigma(E[\hat{g}_{h_\ell}]) + \frac{1}{2}\sigma''(E[\hat{g}_{h_\ell}]) Var[\hat{g}_{h_\ell}] \\ &= \frac{1}{2} + \frac{1}{2} \cdot 0 \cdot Var[\hat{g}_{h_\ell}] \\ &= \frac{1}{2} \end{aligned} \]

This is because we have \(E[\hat{g}_{h_\ell}] = 0\): \[ \begin{aligned} E[\hat{g}_{h_\ell}] &= E\left[\sum_{h_{\ell-1}=1}^{H_{\ell-1}} G_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} z_{h_{\ell-1}}\right] \\ &= H_{\ell-1}E[G_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}]E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] \\ &= H_{\ell-1} \cdot 0 \cdot E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] \\ &= 0 \end{aligned} \]

Then the addition operator

\[ \begin{aligned} E[a_{h_\ell}] &= E\left[\sum_{h_{\ell-1}=1}^{H_{\ell-1}} W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} z_{h_{\ell-1}}\right] \\ &= H_{\ell-1}E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}]E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] \\ &= H_{\ell-1} \cdot 0 \cdot E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] \\ &= 0 \end{aligned} \]

The the multiplication operator

\[ \begin{aligned} E[m_{h_\ell}] &= E\left[\exp\left(\sum_{h_{\ell-1}=1}^{H_{\ell-1}} W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} \log(|z_{h_{\ell-1}}| + \epsilon) \right)\right] \\ &= E\left[\prod_{h_{\ell-1}=1}^{H_{\ell-1}} \exp(W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} \log(|z_{h_{\ell-1}}| + \epsilon)) \right] \\ &= \prod_{h_{\ell-1}=1}^{H_{\ell-1}} E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} \log(|z_{h_{\ell-1}}| + \epsilon)] \\ &= E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} \log(|z_{h_{\ell-1}}| + \epsilon)]^{H_{\ell-1}} \\ &= E\left[(|z_{h_{\ell-1}}| + \epsilon)^{W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}}\right]^{H_{\ell-1}} \\ &= E\left[f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}})\right]^{H_{\ell-1}} \end{aligned} \] Here we define \(f\) as a non-linear transformation function of two independent stocastic variables:

\[ f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}) = (|z_{h_{\ell-1}}| + \epsilon)^{W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}} \]

We then take the second order taylor approximation of \(f\), around \((E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}], E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}])\).

\[ \begin{aligned} E[f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}})] \approx E\Bigg[&f(E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}], E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}])\\ &+ \begin{bmatrix} z_{h_{\ell-1}} - E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] \\ W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} - E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] \end{bmatrix}^T \begin{bmatrix} \frac{\partial f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}})}{\partial z_{h_{\ell-1}}} \\ \frac{\partial f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}})}{\partial W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}} \end{bmatrix} \Bigg\rvert_{ \begin{cases} z_{h_{\ell-1}} = E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] \\ W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} = E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] \end{cases} } \\ &+ \frac{1}{2} \begin{bmatrix} z_{h_{\ell-1}} - E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] \\ W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} - E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] \end{bmatrix}^T \begin{bmatrix} \frac{\partial^2 f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}})}{\partial^2 z_{h_{\ell-1}}} & \frac{\partial^2 f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}})}{\partial z_{h_{\ell-1}} \partial W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}} \\ \frac{\partial^2 f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}})}{\partial z_{h_{\ell-1}} \partial W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}} & \frac{\partial^2 f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}})}{\partial^2 W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}} \end{bmatrix} \Bigg\rvert_{ \begin{cases} z_{h_{\ell-1}} = E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] \\ W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} = E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] \end{cases} } \begin{bmatrix} z_{h_{\ell-1}} - E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] \\ W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} - E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] \end{bmatrix}\Bigg] \end{aligned} \]

Because \(E[z_{h_{\ell-1}} - E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]] = 0\), \(E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} - E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}]] = 0\), and \(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}\) are uncorrelated. This similifies to:

\[ \begin{aligned} E[f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}})] \approx &f(E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}], E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}])\\ &+ \frac{1}{2} Var\begin{bmatrix} z_{h_{\ell-1}} \\ W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} \end{bmatrix}^T \begin{bmatrix} \frac{\partial^2 f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}})}{\partial^2 z_{h_{\ell-1}}} \\ \frac{\partial^2 f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}})}{\partial^2 W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}} \end{bmatrix} \Bigg\rvert_{ \begin{cases} z_{h_{\ell-1}} = E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] \\ W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} = E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] \end{cases} } \end{aligned} \]

Evaluating this yields:

\[ \begin{aligned} E[f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}})] &\approx (|E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]| + \epsilon)^{E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}]} \\ &+ \frac{1}{2} Var[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] (|E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]| + \epsilon)^{E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] - 2} E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] (E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] - 1) \\ &+ \frac{1}{2} Var[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] (|E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]| + \epsilon)^{E[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}]} \log(|E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]| + \epsilon)^2 \\ &=1 + \frac{1}{2} Var[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] \log(|E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]| + \epsilon)^2 \end{aligned} \]

This gives the expectation:

\[ \begin{aligned} E[m_{h_\ell}] &= E\left[f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}})\right]^{H_{\ell-1}} \\ &\approx\left(1 + \frac{1}{2} Var[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] \log(|E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]| + \epsilon)^2\right)^{H_{\ell-1}} \end{aligned} \]

As this expectation is of particuar interrest, we evaluate the error of the approximation, where \(W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} \sim U[-r_w,r_w]\) and \(z_{h_{\ell-1}} \sim U[0, r_z]\). These distributions are what is used in the simple function task is done.

m.expectation.taylor = function (r.w, r.z) {
  w.var = (1/3) * r.w^2;
  z.e = (1/2) * r.z;
  return(1 + 0.5*w.var*log(abs(z.e) + 10^-8)^2);
}
m.expectation.simulation = function (r.w, r.z) {
  w.samples = runif(100000, -r.w, r.w);
  z.samples = runif(100000, 0, r.z);
  f.samples = exp(w.samples * log(z.samples + 10^-8));
  return(mean(f.samples));
}

m.expectation.input = expand.grid(r.w = seq(0.001, 0.5, 0.011), r.z = seq(1, 50, 1))
m.expectation.error = mapply(function(r.w,r.z) {
  return(m.expectation.taylor(r.w, r.z) - m.expectation.simulation(r.w, r.z))
}, m.expectation.input$r.w, m.expectation.input$r.z)
p = ggplot(cbind(m.expectation.input, m.expectation.error), aes(r.w, r.z)) +
  geom_raster(aes(fill = m.expectation.error)) +
  geom_contour(aes(z = m.expectation.error), colour='white')
print(p)

Total expectation

We thus have that the expectation of \(E[y_{h_\ell}]\) is:

\[ \begin{aligned} E[z_{h_\ell}] &= E[g_{h_\ell}] E[a_{h_\ell}] + (1 - E[g_{h_\ell}]) E[m_{h_\ell}] \\ &\approx \frac{1}{2} \cdot 0 + \frac{1}{2} \left(1 + \frac{1}{2} Var[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] \log(|E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]| + \epsilon)^2\right)^{H_{\ell-1}} \end{aligned} \]

This is somewhat problematic, as even in the best case (\(|E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]| + \epsilon = 1\)) we have \(E[y_{h_\ell}] = \frac{1}{2}\).

This problem could be solved, by using a bias parameter. Such that one have:

\[ z_{h_\ell} = g_{h_\ell} a_{h_\ell} + (1 - g_{h_\ell}) (m_{h_\ell} + b_{h_\ell}),\ E[b_{h_\ell}] = -1 \]

However, it still seams problematic as \(\frac{1}{2} Var[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] \log(|E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]| + \epsilon) \approx 0\) only holds for a very small variance of \(W_{h_{\ell}}\) and a very limited range of \(E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]\).

Diriving the variance

Output variance

Assuming for simplicity that \(Cov[a_{h_\ell}, g_{h_\ell}] = 0\), \(Cov[m_{h_\ell}, g_{h_\ell}] = 0\), \(Cov[a_{h_\ell}, m_{h_\ell}] = 0\). Which is definetly not true, because they all depend on \(z_{h_{\ell-1}}\) and addition and multiplication are correlated.

\[ \begin{aligned} Var[z_{h_\ell}] &\approx E[g_{h_\ell}]^2 Var[a_{h_\ell}] + E[1 - g_{h_\ell}]^2 Var[m_{h_\ell}] \\ &+ E[a_{h_\ell}]^2 Var[g_{h_\ell}] + E[m_{h_\ell}]^2 Var[1 - g_{h_\ell}] \\ &+ Var[g_{h_\ell}] Var[a_{h_\ell}] + Var[1 - g_{h_\ell}] Var[m_{h_\ell}] \\ &= E[g_{h_\ell}]^2 Var[a_{h_\ell}] + \left(1 - E[g_{h_\ell}]\right)^2 Var[m_{h_\ell}] \\ &+ E[a_{h_\ell}]^2 Var[g_{h_\ell}] + E[m_{h_\ell}]^2 Var[g_{h_\ell}] \\ &+ Var[g_{h_\ell}] Var[a_{h_\ell}] + Var[g_{h_\ell}] Var[m_{h_\ell}] \end{aligned} \]

Gate Variance

Recall that \(Var[\hat{g}_{h_\ell}] = H_{\ell-1} Var[G_{h_{\ell-1}, h_\ell}] E[z_{h_\ell}^2]\) and that \(E[\hat{g}_{h_\ell}] = 0\).

\[ \begin{aligned} Var[g_{h_\ell}] &= Var[\sigma(\hat{g}_{h_\ell})] \\ &= \sigma'(E[\hat{g}_{h_\ell}])^2 Var[\hat{g}_{h_\ell}] + \frac{1}{2} \sigma''(E[\hat{g}_{h_\ell}])^2 Var[\hat{g}_{h_\ell}]^2 \\ &= \left(\frac{1}{4}\right)^2 Var[\hat{g}_{h_\ell}] + \frac{1}{2} \cdot 0 \cdot Var[\hat{g}_{h_\ell}]^2 \\ &= \frac{1}{16} Var[\hat{g}_{h_\ell}] \\ &=\frac{1}{16} H_{\ell-1} Var\left[G_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}\right] Var[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] \end{aligned} \]

Addition operation

\[ \begin{aligned} Var[a_{h_\ell}] &= Var\left[\sum_{h_{\ell-1}=1}^{H_{\ell-1}} W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} z_{h_{\ell-1}}\right] \\ &= H_{\ell-1} Var\left[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}\right] Var[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] \end{aligned} \]

The same result, was used for the \(Var[\hat{g}_{h_\ell}]\).

Multiplication operation

\[ \begin{aligned} Var[m_{h_\ell}] &= Var\left[\exp\left(\sum_{h_{\ell-1}=1}^{H_{\ell-1}} W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} \log(|z_{h_{\ell-1}}| + \epsilon) \right)\right] \\ &= Var\left[\prod_{h_{\ell-1}=1}^{H_{\ell-1}} (|z_{h_{\ell-1}}| + \epsilon)^{W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}} \right] \\ &= E\left[\left(\prod_{h_{\ell-1}=1}^{H_{\ell-1}} (|z_{h_{\ell-1}}| + \epsilon)^{W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}}\right)^2 \right] - E\left[\prod_{h_{\ell-1}=1}^{H_{\ell-1}} (|z_{h_{\ell-1}}| + \epsilon)^{W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}}\right]^2 \\ &= E\left[\prod_{h_{\ell-1}=1}^{H_{\ell-1}} (|z_{h_{\ell-1}}| + \epsilon)^{2 \cdot W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}} \right] - E\left[\prod_{h_{\ell-1}=1}^{H_{\ell-1}} (|z_{h_{\ell-1}}| + \epsilon)^{W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}}\right]^2 \\ &= E\left[f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, 2 \cdot W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}) \right]^{H_{\ell-1}} - E\left[f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}})\right]^{2\cdot H_{\ell-1}} \end{aligned} \]

We already have from previus results that:

\[ E\left[f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}})\right] \approx 1 + \frac{1}{2} Var[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] \log(|E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]| + \epsilon)^2 \]

By substitution of variable we have that:

\[ \begin{aligned} E\left[f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, 2 \cdot W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}})\right] &\approx 1 + \frac{1}{2} Var[2 \cdot W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] \log(|E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]| + \epsilon)^2 \\ &= \approx 1 + 2 \cdot Var[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] \log(|E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]| + \epsilon)^2 \end{aligned} \] This gives the variance:

\[ \begin{aligned} Var[m_{h_\ell}] &= Var\left[\exp\left(\sum_{h_{\ell-1}=1}^{H_{\ell-1}} W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}} \log(|z_{h_{\ell-1}}| + \epsilon) \right)\right] \\ &= E\left[f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, 2 \cdot W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}) \right]^{H_{\ell-1}} - E\left[f(z_{h_{\ell-1}}, W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}})\right]^{2\cdot H_{\ell-1}} \\ &\approx \left(1 + 2 \cdot Var[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] \log(|E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]| + \epsilon)^2\right)^{H_{\ell-1}} \\ &- \left(1 + \frac{1}{2} \cdot Var[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] \log(|E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]| + \epsilon)^2\right)^{2\cdot H_{\ell-1}} \end{aligned} \]

m.variance.taylor = function (r.w, r.z) {
  w.var = (1/3) * r.w^2;
  z.e = (1/2) * r.z;
  return((1 + 2*w.var*log(abs(z.e) + 10^-8)^2) - (1 + 0.5*w.var*log(abs(z.e) + 10^-8)^2)^2);
}
m.variance.simulation = function (r.w, r.z) {
  w.samples = runif(100000, -r.w, r.w);
  z.samples = runif(100000, 0, r.z);
  f.samples = exp(w.samples * log(z.samples + 10^-8));
  return(var(f.samples));
}

m.variance.input = expand.grid(r.w = seq(0.001, 0.5, 0.011), r.z = seq(1, 50, 1))
m.variance.error = mapply(function(r.w,r.z) {
  return(m.variance.taylor(r.w, r.z) - m.variance.simulation(r.w, r.z))
}, m.variance.input$r.w, m.variance.input$r.z)
p = ggplot(cbind(m.variance.input, m.variance.error), aes(r.w, r.z)) +
  geom_raster(aes(fill = m.variance.error)) +
  geom_contour(aes(z = m.variance.error), colour='white')
print(p)

Total variance

Combining these results we have:

\[ \begin{aligned} Var[z_{h_\ell}] &\approx E[g_{h_\ell}]^2 Var[a_{h_\ell}] + \left(1 - E[g_{h_\ell}]\right)^2 Var[m_{h_\ell}] \\ &+ E[a_{h_\ell}]^2 Var[g_{h_\ell}] + E[m_{h_\ell}]^2 Var[g_{h_\ell}] \\ &+ Var[g_{h_\ell}] Var[a_{h_\ell}] + Var[g_{h_\ell}] Var[m_{h_\ell}] \\ &= \left(\frac{1}{2}\right)^2 Var[a_{h_\ell}] + \left(\frac{1}{2}\right)^2 Var[m_{h_\ell}] \\ &+ 0 \cdot Var[g_{h_\ell}] + E[m_{h_\ell}]^2 Var[g_{h_\ell}] \\ &+ Var[g_{h_\ell}] Var[a_{h_\ell}] + Var[g_{h_\ell}] Var[m_{h_\ell}] \\ &= \frac{1}{4} \left(Var[a_{h_\ell}] + Var[m_{h_\ell}]\right) \\ &+ Var[g_{h_\ell}] \left(Var[a_{h_\ell}] + E[m_{h_\ell}]^2 + Var[m_{h_\ell}]\right) \\ &= \frac{1}{4} \left(Var[a_{h_\ell}] + Var[m_{h_\ell}]\right) \\ &+ Var[g_{h_\ell}] \left(Var[a_{h_\ell}] + E[m_{h_\ell}^2]\right) \end{aligned} \]

As the expressing for \(Var[m_{h_\ell}]\) is rather larger and hard to intrepert, we can instead collect \(Var[a_{h_\ell}]\), \(E[m_{h_\ell}^2]\), and \(E[m_{h_\ell}]^2\).

\[ \begin{aligned} Var[z_{h_\ell}] &\approx \frac{1}{4} \left(Var[a_{h_\ell}] + Var[m_{h_\ell}]\right) \\ &+ Var[g_{h_\ell}] \left(Var[a_{h_\ell}] + E[m_{h_\ell}^2]\right) \\ &= \frac{1}{4}Var[a_{h_\ell}] + \frac{1}{4}E[m_{h_\ell}^2] - \frac{1}{4} E[m_{h_\ell}]^2 \\ &+ Var[g_{h_\ell}] Var[a_{h_\ell}] + Var[g_{h_\ell}]E[m_{h_\ell}^2] \\ &= Var[a_{h_\ell}] \left(\frac{1}{4} + Var[g_{h_\ell}]\right) \\ &+ E[m_{h_\ell}^2] \left(\frac{1}{4} + Var[g_{h_\ell}]\right) - \frac{1}{4} E[m_{h_\ell}]^2 \\ &= \left(Var[a_{h_\ell}] + E[m_{h_\ell}^2]\right) \left(\frac{1}{4} + Var[g_{h_\ell}]\right) - \frac{1}{4} E[m_{h_\ell}]^2 \end{aligned} \]

Inserting \(Var[g_{h_\ell}], Var[a_{h_\ell}], E[m_{h_\ell}^2]]\) this yeids:

\[ \begin{aligned} Var[z_{h_\ell}] &\approx \left(Var[a_{h_\ell}] + E[m_{h_\ell}^2]\right) \left(\frac{1}{4} + Var[g_{h_\ell}]\right) - \frac{1}{4} E[m_{h_\ell}]^2 \\ &= \left(H_{\ell-1} Var[W_{h_{\ell-1},h_\ell}] Var[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] + \left(1 + 2 \cdot Var[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] \log(|E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]| + \epsilon)^2\right)^{H_{\ell-1}}\right)\left(\frac{1}{4} + \frac{1}{16} H_{\ell-1} Var[G_{h_{\ell-1}, h_\ell}] Var[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]\right) \\ &- \frac{1}{4}\left(1 + \frac{1}{2} \cdot Var[W_{h_{\ell}, h_{\ell-1}}] \log(|E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]| + \epsilon)^2\right)^{2\cdot H_{\ell-1}} \end{aligned} \]

Even for the best case, where \(|E[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]| = 1\) (NOTE: this is not a desired property in terms of exploding/vanishing gradient), this shows that it is not possible to maintain variance though the layers:

\[ \begin{aligned} Var[z_{h_\ell}] &= \left(H_{\ell-1} Var[W_{h_{\ell-1},h_\ell}] Var[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] + 1\right)\left(\frac{1}{4} + \frac{1}{16} H_{\ell-1} Var[G_{h_{\ell-1}, h_\ell}]Var[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]\right) - \frac{1}{4} \\ &=\frac{1}{4} H_{\ell-1} Var[W_{h_{\ell-1},h_\ell}] Var[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] + H_{\ell-1}^2 Var[W_{h_{\ell-1},h_\ell}] Var[G_{h_{\ell-1}, h_\ell}] Var[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]^2 + \frac{1}{16} H_{\ell-1} Var[G_{h_{\ell-1}, h_\ell}]Var[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] \\ &= H_{\ell-1} Var[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] \left( \frac{1}{4} Var[W_{h_{\ell-1},h_\ell}] + H_{\ell-1} Var[W_{h_{\ell-1},h_\ell}] Var[G_{h_{\ell-1}, h_\ell}] Var[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] + \frac{1}{16} Var[G_{h_{\ell-1}, h_\ell}]\right) \end{aligned} \] As it can be seen, maintaining variance though the layers (\(Var[z_{h_\ell}] = Var[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]\)) is not possible due to the \(Var[z_{h_{\ell-1}}]^2\) term.

In the very best case where \(Var[z_{h_{\ell-1}}] = 1\), then:

\[ \begin{aligned} 1 &= H_{\ell-1} \left( \frac{1}{4} Var[W_{h_{\ell-1},h_\ell}] + H_{\ell-1} Var[W_{h_{\ell-1},h_\ell}] Var[G_{h_{\ell-1}, h_\ell}] + \frac{1}{16} Var[G_{h_{\ell-1}, h_\ell}]\right) \end{aligned} \]

Using the same variance for both \(W_{h_{\ell-1},h_\ell}\) and \(G_{h_{\ell-1}, h_\ell}\) we have:

\[ \begin{aligned} 1 &= H_{\ell-1} \left( \frac{1}{4} Var[W_{h_{\ell-1},h_\ell}] + H_{\ell-1} Var[W_{h_{\ell-1},h_\ell}]^2 + \frac{1}{16} Var[W_{h_{\ell-1}, h_\ell}]\right) \end{aligned} \]

Solving this yeilds:

\[ Var[W_{h_{\ell-1},h_\ell}] = Var[G_{h_{\ell-1}, h_\ell}] = \frac{-\frac{5}{32} + \sqrt{\frac{1049}{1024}}}{H_{\ell-1}} \approx \frac{0.8558834210}{H_{\ell-1}} \]

Assuming from Glorot, that we would get a similar result for the backward pass. We have:

\[ Var[W_{h_{\ell-1},h_\ell}] = Var[G_{h_{\ell-1}, h_\ell}] \approx \frac{1.711766842}{H_{\ell-1} + H_{\ell}} \]

Backpropergation

We wish to ensure \(E[\delta_{h_\ell}] = 0\) and \(Var[\delta_{h_\ell}] = Var[\delta_{h_{\ell+1}}]\).

We have:

\[ \begin{aligned} \frac{\partial \mathcal{L}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}} &= \delta_{h_\ell} = \sum_{h_{\ell+1}=1}^{H_{\ell+1}} \delta_{h_{\ell+1}} \frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}} \\ \frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}} &= g_{h_{\ell+1}} \frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}} + (1 - g_{h_{\ell+1}}) \frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}} + (a_{h_{\ell+1}} - m_{h_{\ell+1}}) \frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}} \\ \frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}} &= W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}} \\ \frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}} &= m_{h_{\ell+1}} W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}} \frac{\mathrm{abs}'(z_{h_{\ell}})}{|z_{h_{\ell}}| + \epsilon} \\ \frac{\partial g_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}} &= \sigma'(\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}}) G_{h_{\ell+1},h_{\ell}} \end{aligned} \]

Expectation

\[ E[\delta_{h_\ell}] = E\left[\sum_{h_{\ell+1}=1}^{H_{\ell+1}} \delta_{h_{\ell+1}} \frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] = H_{\ell+1} E[\delta_{h_{\ell+1}}] E\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \]

NALU operation

\[ \begin{aligned} E\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &= E[g_{h_{\ell+1}}]E\left[\frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] + E\left[1 - g_{h_{\ell+1}}\right] E\left[\frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] + E\left[a_{h_{\ell+1}} - m_{h_{\ell+1}}\right] E\left[\frac{\partial g_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \\ &= E[g_{h_{\ell+1}}]E\left[\frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] + (E[1] - E[g_{h_{\ell+1}}]) E\left[\frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] + (E[a_{h_{\ell+1}}] - E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}]) E\left[\frac{\partial g_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \\ &= \frac{1}{2}E\left[\frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] + \frac{1}{2} E\left[\frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] - E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}] E\left[\frac{\partial g_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \end{aligned} \]

Addition operator

\[ E\left[\frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] = E[W_{h_{\ell+1},h_\ell}] = 0 \]

Multiplication operator

\[ E\left[\frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] = E{h_{\ell+1}}] E[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}] E\left[ \frac{\mathrm{abs}'(z_{h_{\ell}})}{|z| + \epsilon}\right] = E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}] \cdot 0 \cdot E\left[ \frac{\mathrm{abs}'(z_{h_{\ell}})}{|z| + \epsilon}\right] = 0 \]

Gate

\[ E\left[\frac{\partial g_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] = E[\sigma(\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}}) (1 - \sigma(\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}}))] E[G_{h_{\ell+1},h_{\ell}}] = E[\sigma(\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}}) (1 - \sigma(\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}}))] \cdot 0 = 0 \]

Total expectation

\[ \begin{aligned} E\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &= \frac{1}{2}E\left[\frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] + \frac{1}{2} E\left[\frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] - E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}] E\left[\frac{\partial g_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \\ &= \frac{1}{2}\cdot 0 + \frac{1}{2} \cdot 0 - E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}] \cdot 0 \\ &= 0 \end{aligned} \]

Thus the expectation is as we wish.

Variance

\[ Var[\delta_{h_\ell}] = Var\left[\sum_{h_{\ell+1}=1}^{H_{\ell+1}} \delta_{h_{\ell+1}} \frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] = H_{\ell+1} Var\left[\delta_{h_{\ell+1}} \cdot \frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \]

Assuming \(Cov[\delta_{h_{\ell+1}}, \frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}] = 0\). We have:

\[ Var[\delta_{h_\ell}] = H_{\ell+1} \left(E[\delta_{h_{\ell+1}}]^2 Var\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] + E\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right]^2 Var[\delta_{h_{\ell+1}}] + Var[\delta_{h_{\ell+1}}] Var\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \right) \]

As \(E\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] = 0\) have already been proven, and it is resonable to assume that \(E[\delta_{h_{\ell+1}}] = 0\). This simplifies to:

\[ Var[\delta_{h_\ell}] = H_{\ell+1} Var[\delta_{h_{\ell+1}}] Var\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \]

This means that that the desired property is:

\[ Var\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] = \frac{1}{H_{\ell+1}} \]

NALU operator

\[ \begin{aligned} Var\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &= Var\left[g_{h_{\ell+1}} \frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}} + (1 - g_{h_{\ell+1}}) \frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}} + (a_{h_{\ell+1}} - m_{h_{\ell+1}}) \frac{\partial g_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \\ \end{aligned} \]

Assuming only dependence between \(g_{h_{\ell+1}} \frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\) and \((1 - g_{h_{\ell+1}}) \frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\) this gives:

\[ \begin{aligned} Var\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &\approx Var\left[(a_{h_{\ell+1}} - m_{h_{\ell+1}}) \frac{\partial g_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \\ &+ Var\left[g_{h_{\ell+1}} \frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] + Var\left[(1 - g_{h_{\ell+1}}) \frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] + 2 Cov\left[g_{h_{\ell+1}} \frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}, (1 - g_{h_{\ell+1}}) \frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \end{aligned} \]

Assuming only dependence between \(g_{h_{\ell+1}}\) and \((1 - g_{h_{\ell+1}})\) one have:

\[ \begin{aligned} Cov\left[g_{h_{\ell+1}} \frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}, (1 - g_{h_{\ell+1}}) \frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &\approx E\left[\frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] E\left[\frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] Cov\left[g_{h_{\ell+1}}, (1 - g_{h_{\ell+1}})\right] \\ &= 0 \cdot 0 \cdot Cov\left[g_{h_{\ell+1}}, (1 - g_{h_{\ell+1}})\right] \\ &= 0 \end{aligned} \]

Thus one have:

\[ \begin{aligned} Var\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &\approx Var\left[(a_{h_{\ell+1}} - m_{h_{\ell+1}}) \frac{\partial g_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] + Var\left[g_{h_{\ell+1}} \frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] + Var\left[(1 - g_{h_{\ell+1}}) \frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \end{aligned} \]

Assuming again independence between each term, this can be expressed as:

\[ \begin{aligned} Var\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &\approx E[a_{h_{\ell+1}} - m_{h_{\ell+1}}]^2 Var\left[ \frac{\partial g_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &&+ Var[a_{h_{\ell+1}} - m_{h_{\ell+1}}] E\left[ \frac{\partial g_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right]^2 &&+ Var[a_{h_{\ell+1}} - m_{h_{\ell+1}}] Var\left[ \frac{\partial g_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \\ &+ E[g_{h_{\ell+1}}]^2 Var\left[\frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &&+ Var[g_{h_{\ell+1}}] E\left[\frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right]^2 &&+ Var\left[\frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] Var[g_{h_{\ell+1}}] \\ &+ E[1 - g_{h_{\ell+1}}]^2 Var\left[\frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &&+ Var[1 - g_{h_{\ell+1}}] E\left[\frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right]^2 &&+ Var[1 - g_{h_{\ell+1}}] Var\left[\frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \end{aligned} \]

Inserting the definities for the expectations that have already been derived to a simple value, one gets:

\[ \begin{aligned} Var\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &\approx E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}]^2 Var\left[ \frac{\partial g_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &&+ Var[a_{h_{\ell+1}} - m_{h_{\ell+1}}] \cdot 0 &&+ Var[a_{h_{\ell+1}} - m_{h_{\ell+1}}] Var\left[ \frac{\partial g_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \\ &+ \frac{1}{4} Var\left[\frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &&+ Var[g_{h_{\ell+1}}] \cdot 0 &&+ Var\left[\frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] Var[g_{h_{\ell+1}}] \\ &+ \frac{1}{4} Var\left[\frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &&+ Var[g_{h_{\ell+1}}] \cdot 0 &&+ Var[ g_{h_{\ell+1}}] Var\left[\frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \end{aligned} \]

Collecting the variances of the derivaties:

\[ \begin{aligned} Var\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &\approx \left(E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}]^2 + Var[a_{h_{\ell+1}} - m_{h_{\ell+1}}]\right) Var\left[\frac{\partial g_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \\ &+ \left(\frac{1}{4} + Var[g_{h_{\ell+1}}]\right) Var\left[\frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \\ &+ \left(\frac{1}{4} + Var[g_{h_{\ell+1}}]\right) Var\left[\frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \end{aligned} \]

Assuming again \(Cov[a_{h_{\ell+1}}, m_{h_{\ell+1}}] = 0\):

\[ \begin{aligned} E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}]^2 + Var[a_{h_{\ell+1}} - m_{h_{\ell+1}}] &\approx E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}]^2 + Var[a_{h_{\ell+1}}] + Var[ m_{h_{\ell+1}}] \\ &= E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}]^2 + Var[a_{h_{\ell+1}}] + E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}^2] - E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}]^2 \\ &= Var[a_{h_{\ell+1}}] + E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}^2] \end{aligned} \]

\[ \begin{aligned} Var\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &\approx \left(E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}^2] + Var[a_{h_{\ell+1}}]\right) Var\left[\frac{\partial g_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \\ &+ \left(\frac{1}{4} + Var[g_{h_{\ell+1}}]\right) Var\left[\frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \\ &+ \left(\frac{1}{4} + Var[g_{h_{\ell+1}}]\right) Var\left[\frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] \end{aligned} \]

Addtion operator

\[ Var\left[\frac{\partial a_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] = Var[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}] \]

Multiplication operator

\[ \begin{aligned} Var\left[\frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &= Var\left[m_{h_{\ell+1}} W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}} \frac{\mathrm{abs}'(z_{h_{\ell}})}{|z_{h_{\ell}}| + \epsilon}\right] \end{aligned} \]

Assuming independence between all terms:

\[ \begin{aligned} Var\left[\frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &= E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}^2] E[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}^2] E\left[\left( \frac{\mathrm{abs}'(z_{h_{\ell}})}{|z_{h_{\ell}}| + \epsilon}\right)^2\right] - E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}]^2 E[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}]^2 E\left[ \frac{\mathrm{abs}'(z_{h_{\ell}})}{|z_{h_{\ell}}| + \epsilon}\right]^2 \\ &= E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}^2] Var[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}] E\left[\left( \frac{\mathrm{abs}'(z_{h_{\ell}})}{|z_{h_{\ell}}| + \epsilon}\right)^2\right] - E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}]^2 \cdot 0 \cdot E\left[ \frac{\mathrm{abs}'(z_{h_{\ell}})}{|z_{h_{\ell}}| + \epsilon}\right]^2 \end{aligned} \]

Using taylor approximation:

\[ E\left[\left( \frac{\mathrm{abs}'(z_{h_{\ell}})}{|z| + \epsilon}\right)^2\right] \approx\frac{1}{\left(|E[z_{h_{\ell}}]| + \epsilon\right)^2} + \frac{1}{2} \frac{6}{\left(|E[z_{h_{\ell}}]| + \epsilon\right)^4} Var[z_{h_{\ell}}] = \frac{1}{\left(|E[z_{h_{\ell}}]| + \epsilon\right)^2} + \frac{3}{\left(|E[z_{h_{\ell}}]| + \epsilon\right)^4} Var[z_{h_{\ell}}] \]

Thus the variance is:

\[ Var\left[\frac{\partial m_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] = E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}^2] Var[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}] \left(\frac{1}{\left(|E[z_{h_{\ell}}]| + \epsilon\right)^2} + \frac{3}{\left(|E[z_{h_{\ell}}]| + \epsilon\right)^4} Var[z_{h_{\ell}}]\right) \]

Gate

Assuming \(Cov[\sigma'(\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}}), G_{h_{\ell+1},h_{\ell}}] = 0\):

\[ \begin{aligned} Var\left[\frac{\partial g_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &= E[\sigma'(\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}})]^2 Var[G_{h_{\ell+1},h_{\ell}}] + Var[\sigma'(\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}})] E[G_{h_{\ell+1},h_{\ell}}]^2 + Var[\sigma'(\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}})] Var[G_{h_{\ell+1},h_{\ell}}] \\ &= E[\sigma'(\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}})]^2 Var[G_{h_{\ell+1},h_{\ell}}] + Var[\sigma'(\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}})] \cdot 0 + Var[\sigma'(\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}})] Var[G_{h_{\ell+1},h_{\ell}}] \\ &= \left(E[\sigma'(\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}})]^2 + Var[\sigma'(\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}})]\right) Var[G_{h_{\ell+1},h_{\ell}}] \\ &= E[\sigma'(\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}})^2] Var[G_{h_{\ell+1},h_{\ell}}] \end{aligned} \]

Using taylor approximation:

\[ \begin{aligned} E[\sigma'(\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}})^2] &\approx \sigma'(E[\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}}])^2 + \frac{1}{2} \frac{\partial^2 \sigma'(x)^2}{\partial x^2} \Big\rvert_{x=E[\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}}]} Var[\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}}] \\ &= \frac{1}{8} - \frac{1}{32} Var[\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}}] \end{aligned} \]

\[ \begin{aligned} Var\left[\frac{\partial g_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &= \left(\frac{1}{8} - \frac{1}{32} Var[\hat{g}_{h_{\ell+1}}]\right) Var[G_{h_{\ell+1},h_{\ell}}] \\ &= \left(\frac{1}{8} - \frac{1}{32} H_{\ell} Var\left[G_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right] Var[z_{h_{\ell}}]\right) Var[G_{h_{\ell+1},h_{\ell}}] \end{aligned} \]

Total variance

Inserting the variance results:

\[ \begin{aligned} Var\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &\approx \left(E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}^2] + Var[a_{h_{\ell+1}}]\right) \left(\frac{1}{8} - \frac{1}{32} H_{\ell} Var\left[G_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right] Var[z_{h_{\ell}}]\right) Var[G_{h_{\ell+1},h_{\ell}}] \\ &+ \left(\frac{1}{4} + Var[g_{h_{\ell+1}}]\right) Var[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}] \\ &+ \left(\frac{1}{4} + Var[g_{h_{\ell+1}}]\right) E[m_{h_{\ell+1}}^2] Var[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}] \left(\frac{1}{\left(|E[z_{h_{\ell}}]| + \epsilon\right)^2} + \frac{3}{\left(|E[z_{h_{\ell}}]| + \epsilon\right)^4} Var[z_{h_{\ell}}]\right) \end{aligned} \]

Inserting variance and expectation results from the forward pass:

\[ \begin{aligned} Var\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &\approx \left(\left(1 + 2 \cdot Var[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}] \log(|E[z_{h_{\ell}}]| + \epsilon)^2\right)^{H_{\ell}} + H_{\ell} Var\left[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right] Var[z_{h_{\ell}}]\right) \left(\frac{1}{8} - \frac{1}{32} H_{\ell} Var\left[G_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right] Var[z_{h_{\ell}}]\right) Var[G_{h_{\ell+1},h_{\ell}}] \\ &+ \left(\frac{1}{4} + \frac{1}{16} H_{\ell} Var\left[G_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right] Var[z_{h_{\ell}}]\right) Var[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}] \\ &+ \left(\frac{1}{4} + \frac{1}{16} H_{\ell} Var\left[G_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right] Var[z_{h_{\ell}}]\right) \left(1 + 2 \cdot Var[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}] \log(|E[z_{h_{\ell}}]| + \epsilon)^2\right)^{H_{\ell}} Var[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}] \left(\frac{1}{\left(|E[z_{h_{\ell}}]| + \epsilon\right)^2} + \frac{3}{\left(|E[z_{h_{\ell}}]| + \epsilon\right)^4} Var[z_{h_{\ell}}]\right) \end{aligned} \]

In the case of \(|E[z_{h_{\ell}}]|\) the variance will explode. This is yet another reason to use the NALU-safe variant.

In the best case where \(|E[z_{h_{\ell}}]| = 1\):

\[ \begin{aligned} Var\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &\approx \left(1 + H_{\ell} Var\left[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right] Var[z_{h_{\ell}}]\right) \left(\frac{1}{8} - \frac{1}{32} H_{\ell} Var\left[G_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right] Var[z_{h_{\ell}}]\right) Var[G_{h_{\ell+1},h_{\ell}}] \\ &+ \left(\frac{1}{4} + \frac{1}{16} H_{\ell} Var\left[G_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right] Var[z_{h_{\ell}}]\right) Var[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}] \\ &+ \left(\frac{1}{4} + \frac{1}{16} H_{\ell} Var\left[G_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right] Var[z_{h_{\ell}}]\right) Var[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}] \left(1 + 3 \cdot Var[z_{h_{\ell}}]\right) \end{aligned} \]

In the best case where the input variance is one:

\[ \begin{aligned} Var\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &\approx \left(1 + H_{\ell} Var\left[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right]\right) \left(\frac{1}{8} - \frac{1}{32} H_{\ell} Var\left[G_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right]\right) Var[G_{h_{\ell+1},h_{\ell}}] \\ &+ \left(\frac{1}{4} + \frac{1}{16} H_{\ell} Var\left[G_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right]\right) Var[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}] \\ &+ \left(\frac{1}{4} + \frac{1}{16} H_{\ell} Var\left[G_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right]\right) Var[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}] \cdot 4 \\ &= \left(1 + H_{\ell} Var\left[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right]\right) \left(\frac{1}{8} - \frac{1}{32} H_{\ell} Var\left[G_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right]\right) Var[G_{h_{\ell+1},h_{\ell}}] \\ &+ \left(\frac{1}{4} + \frac{1}{16} H_{\ell} Var\left[G_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right]\right) Var[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}] \cdot 5 \end{aligned} \]

Setting \(Var\left[G_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right] = Var\left[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right]\):

\[ \begin{aligned} Var\left[\frac{\partial z_{h_{\ell+1}}}{\partial z_{h_\ell}}\right] &\approx \left(1 + H_{\ell} Var\left[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right]\right) \left(\frac{1}{8} - \frac{1}{32} H_{\ell} Var\left[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right]\right) Var[W_{h_{\ell+1},h_{\ell}}] \\ &+ \left(\frac{1}{4} + \frac{1}{16} H_{\ell} Var\left[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}\right]\right) Var[W_{h_{\ell+1}, h_{\ell}}] \cdot 5 \end{aligned} \]
